cs.LO, cs.CL, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the Lambek Calculus, a logical system, and presents a categorical semantics for it. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper discusses the extension of the Lambek Calculus with modalities, which can be applied to natural language processing. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with type systems and properties of type systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the Lambek Calculus has been used in natural language processing and computational linguistics, which are areas of AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the syntactic details of the Lambek Calculus and its extension with modalities, which can be seen as a study of the structure and behavior of these systems.
